  "url": "RationalExponents.html#section-6-3-exercises-4-4",
  "type": "Exercise",
  "number": "6.3.7.37",
  "title": "",
  "body": "In the 1970s, Jared Diamond studied the number of bird species on small islands near New Guinea. He found that larger islands support a larger number of different species, according to the formula where is the number of species on an island of area square kilometers. (Source: Chapman and Reiss, 1992)  Fill in the table.                Graph the function on your calculator for .  How many species of birds would you expect to find on Manus Island, with an area of 2100 square kilometers? On Lavongai, whose area is 1140 square kilometers?  How large must an island be in order to support 200 different species of bird?                 power function  81, 71  126,000 sq km  "
